Biomedical Knowledge Graph Triplet Extraction from PubMed Sentences
Course: Deep Learning Methods for Biomedical Applications with PyTorch
Date: May 2026
Tags: Python PyTorch Deep Learning Biomedical Healthcare AI Knowledge Graphs Transformers Machine Learning Data Science
For this project, I built a biomedical NLP pipeline to extract subject-relation-object triplets from PubMed-style sentences using two annotated datasets: ADKG, focused on Alzheimer’s disease, and MDKG, focused on mental disorders. I started with exploratory data analysis to understand entity types, relation types, sentence density, and relation distance, then converted the raw annotations into model-ready formats. For the main model, I trained and evaluated a SpERT baseline for named entity recognition and relation extraction. For the extension, I fine-tuned a T5-small generative model to produce biomedical triplets directly as text and compared strict vs. relaxed triplet matching. This project helped me practice deep learning, biomedical NLP, model evaluation, error analysis, and building an end-to-end machine learning workflow from raw data to final results.

